oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Logging camp at Betts Springs
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Photograph of teams of oxen used for hauling logs at Betts Springs. Two unidentified men are pictured, one standing under a doorway on left, and another riding an ox on right. Text at the bottom of the photograph reads: "Logging camp, Betts Springs, 5 miles of Jackson, 1889."
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Oxen; Men
